{"id":"compose-course-discussion","domain":"education","difficulty":"hard","pass":false,"score":0.8,"reasoning":"4/5 fields correct. Mismatches: contentType (expected: \"education-discussion\", got: \"social-community\")","expected":{"contentType":"education-discussion","structure":"thread","mechanics":["post","vote","reply"],"boundary":"ask","scale":5},"actual":"```json\n{\"contentType\":\"social-community\",\"structure\":\"thread\",\"mechanics\":[\"post\",\"reply\",\"vote\"],\"boundary\":\"ask\",\"scale\":\"5\"}\n```\n\n**Reasoning:**\n\n- **contentType: `social-community`** — Not `social` (which would auto-group with social feeds) or `education` (which would incorrectly group with education-study). The hyphenated variant signals that this is community discussion infrastructure, distinct from individual study reflection. This prevents unwanted auto-grouping when both modules connect to a shared parent.\n\n- **structure: `thread`** — Students create nested replies to discussion topics. Thread structure is the correct primitive for branching conversations.\n\n- **mechanics: `[\"post\",\"reply\",\"vote\"]`** — Students create top-level topics (`post`), respond to each other (`reply`), and upvote contributions (`vote`). No `track` or `chart` — this is synchronous discussion, not temporal data tracking.\n\n- **boundary: `ask`** — Students must sign up, which means personal/identity data is collected. Sharing community participation requires consent. This prevents leakage of discussion history without user agreement.\n\n- **scale: `5`** — A self-contained module with internal loops. Students join, create topics, reply, vote — all within a cohesive interactive unit. Could operate standalone or compose into larger education platforms (S6+).","durationMs":5431}
